---
import AboutImage from '../image/img-selff.jpg'
---

<style>
  
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    color: #0e0101;
    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
    background-color: rgba(39, 42, 41, 0.704);
    border-radius: 15px;
  }

  /* ── Hero row: photo + intro ── */
  .hero {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .image {
    width: 140px;
    height: 140px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    border: 2px solid rgba(54, 110, 100, 0.5);
  }

  .intro-text h1 {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .intro-text .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent, #46A695);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent, #46A695);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .intro-text p {
    font-size: 1.23rem;
    /* line-height: 2rem; */
    color: var(--color-text-muted, #ffffff);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Divider ── */
  .divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  /* ── Section blocks ── */
  .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent, #46A695);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }

  .section p {
    /* font-size: 0.95rem; */
    /* line-height: 1.75; */
    color: var(--color-text-muted, #636370);
    margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
  }

  /* ── Interests pill row ── */
  .pills {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .pill {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(70, 166, 149, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(70, 166, 149, 0.3);
    color: var(--color-accent, #46A695);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  /* ── Publication card ── */
  .pub-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pub-card .pub-title {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .pub-card .pub-venue {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted, #636370);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Currently banner ── */
  .now-banner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    background: rgba(70, 166, 149, 0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(70, 166, 149, 0.2);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .now-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent, #46A695);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--color-accent, #46A695);
    animation: pulse 2s infinite;
  }

  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50%       { opacity: 0.3; }
  }

  .now-banner p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #c0c0c0;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── MOBILE ── */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .container {
      padding: 1.25rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    /* Stack photo above text on mobile */
    .hero {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }

    .image {
      width: 110px;
      height: 110px;
    }

    .intro-text h1 {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
    }

    .pills {
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="container">

  <!-- Hero: photo + intro -->
  <div class="hero">
    <img class="image" src={AboutImage.src} alt="Vishnu Kadam" />
    <div class="intro-text">
      <h1>Vishnu Kadam</h1>
      <span class="tag">BS-MS · IISER Pune</span>
      <p>
        I'm a BS-MS graduate from the Indian Institute of Science Education and
        Research, Pune. My interests lie in all things deep learning — from
        theory to the latest applications. Recently I've been drawn to
        Mechanistic Interpretability and am working my way through it seriously.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- <hr class="divider" /> -->

  <!-- Current focus -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Now</p>
    <div class="now-banner">
      <div class="now-dot"></div>
      <p>
        Investigating mechanistic interpretability techniques on AI weather
        models — trying to uncover what these models actually learn internally.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Interests -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Interests</p>
    <div class="pills">
      <span class="pill">Mechanistic Interpretability</span>
      <span class="pill">Deep Learning </span>
      <span class="pill">Weather Prediction</span>
      <span class="pill">NLP</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Research -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Publication</p>
    
    <div class="pub-card">
      <p class="pub-title">CurvePotGCN – A graph neural network to predict protein–protein interactions using surface curvature and electrostatic potential as node-features</p>
      <p class="pub-venue"> 2026 <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12039-025-02459-7" style="color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration:none;">PDF ↗</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Projects -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Projects</p>
    <h2>Weather Prediction · Master's Thesis</h2>
    <p>
      Started as a curriculum project and grew into my thesis. I trained and
      fine-tuned an SFNO-based weather prediction model, then benchmarked its
      regional forecasting capabilities after fine-tuning. Currently extending
      this with mechanistic interpretability to understand what the model has
      actually learned.
    </p>
    

    
    <h2>Protein–Protein Interaction</h2>
    <p>
      My first research project was deep learning for protein–protein interaction
      under Dr. Arnab Goswami. I handled everything end-to-end — dataset
      creation, model architecture decisions, training, and benchmarking. It was
      my first real exposure to what research actually demands, and it led to my
      first publication.
    </p>

    <h2>Diffusion Models</h2>
    <p>
      An in-depth dive into score-based diffusion — I implemented annealed
      Langevin dynamics from scratch and built extensive visualisations to
      develop an intuition for the process.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>